        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 25 at 2:48PM EDT by NWS Charleston WV</headline>
        <description>At 248 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Baltimore, or 7 miles north of Lancaster, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Somerset, Thornport, Harbor Hills, Thornville, and Glenford.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
